summary:
My work is centered around fostering ideas and policies that serve to rethink the current socio-economic system in a way that  benefits people, nature and provides for the promise of a more sustainable future. Urban planning and built environment are the main domains of my focus, as I believe that places we live, play and work in hold a great potential to drive change. Currently, working at a philanthropic organization gives me an amazing opportunity to partner and work together with very inspiring, driven and strong organizations across Europe which are making sure that decarbonization of built environment is coupled with just transition efforts to shape a better future for our planet. 

I am always happy to converse around cities, buildings, their impact, underlying and unseen socio-economic structures- so don't be shy to reach out!
